	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well its truly your decision, we can only input.<br><br>I chose a Wood elf ok stats (105 dex) and good starting area. The one thing i look back apon is that i have preety chessy Strentgh, 80 is my base str but there are many str buffers it was no problem, and now i have 123 str and 154dex at level 29 so did ok.<br><br>Halflings hide and sneak at birth, in the best starting location and good str and dex. what else can we say.<br><br>Barbarian higest str lowest dex Which can cause problems later on in life.And are night blind. and i cant see a 7ft dude backstabbing kinda sounds funny, just my opinion<br><br>Dark Elf Born to the night, the tier'dal rogue familiy. the worst str (60) and not so good dex (85) but real fun roleplay.<br><br>Dwarf seconond higest str (90) for the Rogues and great dex (100)<br><br>Gnome small stature but large of brain (60)str but good dex(95) and on another plus tinkering at level 16 which is a money maker what i have heard.<br><br>And there is human pretty standerd<br><br>Backy Impailer<br>Level 29<br>Legion of Nox<br>Cazic-thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
