<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=100827392360707></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100827392360707><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100827392360707>RE: The Age Old Question...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100827392360707#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>300 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 13th 3:05 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok don't mind me, but I'm just going to go over your post with a fine steel comb:<br><br>Wood elf: Thats 105 AGI, not dex; they have 90 dex; Dexterity is much more important to a rogue than agility (well, people could argue that AGI is better, but even Verant recognizes that the rogue's role is damage-DEALING above all else, which would include improving your STR and DEX)<br><br>Halflings: Hide and sneak at birth, but any other race can get 50 in sneak'n'hide in no time. They have excellent AGI and DEX (105 and 100, respectively), but how is 70 STR good? I'm assuming you had a typo there. Rivervale is CLOSE to the starting location, which is up to debate but in my opinion is anywhere in the Freeport to Felwithe area. Reason being it's a huge expanse of easily travelled land with hundreds of opportunities for low-levels.<br><br>Barbarian: Even though they get the lowest DEX, it's still 80, which is average or above average. You can put most your bonus points into it and still have high points in the other stats. And actually, starting stats cause LESS problems the further in life you get; because the higher-level you get, the more opportunites you get to 'fix' all your stats by getting equipment. Role-playing wise, they wouldn't seem too sneaky, but hey, it's still possible. And night-blind: so what? Crank up the gamma, get a mask of deception, or just ignore it; it doesn't really affect me that much.<br><br>Dark elf: Yup, yup. Don't forget they get 100 AGI, which almost (well not really) redeems their weaknesses. These are good for a challenge and role-playing.<br><br>Dwarf: Similar and opposite to Barbarians in many ways. Instead of tall, they're short. They take after the barb's STR and STA, but not quite as high. And they switch AGI and DEX; instead of the barbie's 92AGI 80DEX they have 80AGI 100DEX. In my opinion they are still the best suited stat-wise for a rogue, and fit the role-playing bill nicely as well. Infravision so they're not blind (I got a mask of deception for mine anyway).<br><br>Gnome: Yup yup again. Don't forget the 95 AGI.<br><br>Human: Exactly.<br><br>This, of course, was all just my opinion (except factual information about stats). Hope you don't feel like I'm knockin' ya, Backy.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD (Un-retired!)<br>36th Dwarf Rogue<br>Fury Fighters<br>Xegony<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
