	   <tr><td colspan=2>And with all due respect, the wise Daviv McD is quite right.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, once again he neglects the ever versitile and cunning half-elf.  Although not as strong or high in stamina as barbarians or dwarves the half-elf has great flexibility.  Infravision, high starting AGI and DEX, 3 different starting locations, and better looks. Half-elf rogues have all the advantages of elves but with more strength.  If you are into role playing then do not pass over the half-elf.  If you are strictly a stat minded power gamer choose a dwarf.  At least with a dwarf you won't block the passage ways.<br><br>Slipskin Ashenheart<br>30 Rogue, Half-Elf (and proud of it)<br>Bertoxx Server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
