	   <tr><td colspan=2>Heh sorry Slipskin. I was correcting and commenting on the races he originally noted. Didn't mean to leave out half-elves; it was a complete mistake...heh. Well as long as I'm typing I'll put in my opinion on them.<br><br>Infravision is always nice. High starting AGI and DEX, but not the highest. Halflings beat them in that category, and yet half-elves have the same low STR and even lower STA. They do, however, have quite a few redeeming qualities. Better looks of course (although with Luclin models pretty much any race but gnomes look great enough to not really care that much). Role-playing they fit well, although I always thought that rogues specifically could be role-played by any race (the definition of rogue is &quot;acting independently and using unorthodox methods that often cause trouble...different and unwanted, and often dangerous or destructive&quot;, NOT &quot;a sneaky little thief who can fit through cracks and move like the wind.&quot; So basically any race can fit that description as long as they don't feel like playing by the rules.) Half-elves also get 3 starting locations to choose from (why you'd want to start at Qeynos when you can start at Freeport or GFay, I don't know ;) ). Finally, and probably most overlooked, is the half-elves CHA. Only wood elves, half-elves, and humans have a CHA of 75. This gives them an advantage in prices to slightly counterbalance their disadvantages. (NOTE: Sneaking behind an NPC will change it's con to indifferent and will allow you to trade if you were unable to before. However, CHA still plays a role in how MUCH they will charge you. The reason is probably because CHA includes more than looks, like your manner of speech. So even when they can't see you, they can still like your voice.) Well there it all is. Keep in mind, newbies, these are just the facts as I see them. Choose whatever race you wanna be; if this info doesn't even affect your decision that's cool. I didn't choose a dwarf because I think he's best suited for the job stat-wise; I picked him cuz I wanted something near Freeport besides a boring human, and a dwarf rogue seemed an unusual combo at the time.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD (Un-retired!)<br>36th Dwarf Rogue<br>Fury Fighters<br>Xegony<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
